{"title_page": "Le\u00e1nyfalu", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n|timezone=[[Central European Time|CET]]\n|utc_offset=+1\n|timezone_DST=[[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST=+2\n|pushpin_map            =Hungary \n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location of Le\u00e1nyfalu\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|official_name=Le\u00e1nyfalu\n|map=\n|subdivision_type1=[[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[Pest (county)|Pest]]\n|area_total_km2=15.37\n|population_total=3159\n|population_footnotes=\n|population_as_of=2007\n|population_density_km2=168.45\n|postal_code_type=[[Postal code]]\n|postal_code=2016\n|area_code=26\n|coordinates            = {{coord|47|43|36|N|19|5|22|E|region:HU_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|website= {{URL|http://www.leanyfalu.hu/}}\n}}\n\n'''Le\u00e1nyfalu''' is a riverside village in [[Pest (county)|Pest]] county, [[Budapest metropolitan area]], [[Hungary]]. It is just north of [[Szentendre]] located at {{coord|47|43|36|N|19|5|22|E |region:HU_type:city}}. Located between the branch of the Small [[Danube]] ([[Kis-Duna]]) and the spurs of the [[Visegr\u00e1d Hills]], Le\u00e1nyfalu stretches some 5&nbsp;kilometres in length. It was declared a holiday resort in 1936 and became an independent municipality in 1949.{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n\nTo visit Le\u00e1nyfalu from [[Budapest]], take the local [[Vol\u00e1n]] buses on the Budapest [[\u00dajpest V\u00e1roskapu]] \u2013 [[Tahit\u00f3tfalu]] \u2013 [[Visegr\u00e1d]] \u2013 [[Esztergom]] line, which leaves around one to three times per hour. By automobile, take route&nbsp;11 passing through Szentendre.\n\n== Trivia ==\n* Some of the best Hungarian writers, artists, and musicians have retreated to Le\u00e1nyfalu.{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n* The village received media attention in the [[Ciaran Tobin extradition case]].{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu1.jpg\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu2.jpg\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu3.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.leanyfalu.hu/}}\n* [http://leanyfalu.lap.hu/ Le\u00e1nyfalu Link Collection (Hungarian Only)]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leanyfalu}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Pest County]]\n\n\n{{Pest-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n|timezone=[[Central European Time|CET]]\n|utc_offset=+1\n|timezone_DST=[[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST=+2\n|pushpin_map            =Hungary \n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location of Le\u00e1nyfalu\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|official_name=Le\u00e1nyfalu\n|map=\n|subdivision_type1=[[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[Pest (county)|Pest]]\n|area_total_km2=15.37\n|population_total=3159\n|population_footnotes=\n|population_as_of=2007\n|population_density_km2=168.45\n|postal_code_type=[[Postal code]]\n|postal_code=2016\n|area_code=26\n|coordinates            = {{coord|47|43|36|N|19|5|22|E|region:HU_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|website= {{URL|http://www.leanyfalu.hu/}}\n}}\n\n'''Le\u00e1nyfalu''' is a riverside village in [[Pest (county)|Pest]] county, [[Budapest metropolitan area]], [[Hungary]]. It is just north of [[Szentendre]] located at {{coord|47|43|36|N|19|5|22|E |region:HU_type:city}}. Located between the branch of the Small [[Danube]] ([[Kis-Duna]]) and the spurs of the [[Visegr\u00e1d Hills]], Le\u00e1nyfalu stretches some 5&nbsp;kilometres in length. It was declared a holiday resort in 1936 and became an independent municipality in 1949.{{Cn|date=January 2017}}\n\nTo visit Le\u00e1nyfalu from [[Budapest]], take the local [[Vol\u00e1n]] buses on the Budapest [[\u00dajpest V\u00e1roskapu]] \u2013 [[Tahit\u00f3tfalu]] \u2013 [[Visegr\u00e1d]] \u2013 [[Esztergom]] line, which leaves around one to three times per hour. By automobile, take route&nbsp;11 passing through Szentendre.\n\n== Trivia ==\n* Some of the best Hungarian writers, artists, and musicians have retreated to Le\u00e1nyfalu.{{Cn|date=January 2017}}\n* The village received media attention in the [[Ciaran Tobin extradition case]].{{Cn|date=January 2017}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu1.jpg\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu2.jpg\nImage:Le\u00e1nyfalu3.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.leanyfalu.hu/}}\n* [http://leanyfalu.lap.hu/ Le\u00e1nyfalu Link Collection (Hungarian Only)]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leanyfalu}}\n\n\n{{Pest-geo-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Pest County]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Le%C3%A1nyfalu"}
